title: Track difference
htmlContent:
Track difference

The track width difference is the angle (2) between the contact lines (1,3) of the wheel contact points of the left front and rear wheels and right front and rear wheels.

The angle is positive if the front track width is smaller than the rear track width and negative if the front track is greater than the rear track width.

The track width difference is generally give in degrees. If the wheel base is known, length data is also possible.
